modules.description: Provides operations for building and traversing lazy prefix trees, including insertion of key-value pairs, lookup by key, and efficient traversal of shared prefixes. Works with immutable tree structures where nodes are evaluated on demand. Used to implement efficient, memory-conscious string-based indexing in applications like autocompletion and routing tables.

Provides operations to construct, query, and modify lazy tries, which are tree-like structures mapping lists of keys to values. Works with tuples of key-value pairs and lazy lists of child nodes, enabling efficient path-based access and modification. Supports setting and retrieving values along paths, pruning branches, and grafting subtries, useful for implementing configuration hierarchies or symbolic expression parsing.
